An edition of the Fernaig MS, compiled by Donnchadh Mac Rath (Duncan MacRae) in the late 17th century.
The MS contains 57 poems, most of which are religious or have strong religious overtones.
There are 11 political poems (with religious overtones) relating to the Jacobite cause, seemingly composed by Donnchadh himself.
