Moireach&rsquo;s and Rothach&rsquo;s war poetry is also important. Rothach&rsquo;s is of particular interest, as it is written in a form of free-verse that did not become popular in Gaelic until 40 years later. Moireach&rsquo;s war poems are in non-Gaelic verse forms. His other verse is more conventional.
